quizDraft.prompt:
What does this code print when `score = 100`?

```python
score = 100

if score >= 60:
    print("Pass")
elif score == 100:
    print("Perfect")
else:
    print("Fail")
```

Consider this code:

```python
if n == 0:
    print("zero")
elif n <= 10:
    print("small")
else:
    print("big")
```

Which values print `zero`? Choose all that apply.

quizDraft.solutionCode:
age = int(input())

if age < 0:
    print("Invalid")
elif age < 13:
    print("Child")
else:
    print("Older")

score = int(input())

if score == 100:
    print("Perfect")
elif score >= 60:
    print("Pass")
else:
    print("Fail")

text = input()

if text == "":
    print("Empty")
elif text == "yes":
    print("Confirmed")
else:
    print("Other")

n = int(input())

if n == 0:
    print("Zero")
elif n <= 10:
    print("Small")
else:
    print("Large")

code = int(input())

if code < 0:
    print("Invalid")
elif code == 0:
    print("Start")
else:
    print("Continue")
